From 44fc1f7088349bd5211b5e906e2aa32533673adf Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: korchasa <korchasa@icloud.com>
Date: Fri, 12 Jun 2026 12:12:02 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] feat(engine): journal state snapshots with crash-safe
 compaction (FR-E83)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Add a state_snapshot journal event (snapshot_version 1, full replayed run
model, node_dirs, events_covered) and extend the single replayer in
src/state/run-journal.ts to seed from the latest valid snapshot, applying
only subsequent events; journals without snapshots replay exactly as
before, and unsupported snapshot versions fail replay naming the journal
path and version.

New shared core src/state/journal-compaction.ts implements the crash-safe
protocol — replay, write journal.jsonl.tmp (one snapshot, zero tail),
fsync, copy to journal.jsonl.bak (one generation), atomic rename — with a
test-only fault hook; crash-injection tests cover every step boundary.
Refuses when the run lock is held by a live process or the journal does
not replay cleanly. Replay returns a canonically-ordered RunState so the
snapshot+tail vs full-replay equivalence holds as JSON byte equality.

Engine auto-compacts at level/chunk completion only (never mid-node) when
events since the last snapshot exceed the new validated
defaults.journal_compaction_threshold_events (0 disables, default 500),
emitting a single verbose line. New CLI subcommand
`flowai-workflow runs compact --workflow <dir> --run <id> [--dry-run]`
prints the exact one-line summary and exits non-zero with one-line errors.

Docs: FR-E83 registered in SRS (01-execution-model) + FR map + index; SDS
journal/recovery contract moved to new design-engine/06-journal-durability
section file (04-data-and-logic was at its token-budget ceiling).

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
