+<!-- section file — index: [documents/design-engine.md](../design-engine.md) -->
+
+# SDS Engine — Journal Durability & Compaction
+
+Recovery contract for the run journal: durable lifecycle replay (FR-E69)
+and state snapshots with crash-safe compaction (FR-E83). Data entities and
+logic split out of [04-data-and-logic.md](04-data-and-logic.md) to fit the
+docs token budget.
+
+## Data
+
+- Run Journal: JSONL (`<workflow>/runs/<run-id>/journal.jsonl`). Append-only
+  recovery contract; replay derives `RunState` from empty memory (FR-E69) or
+  from the latest `state_snapshot` event (FR-E83). Siblings after
+  compaction: `journal.jsonl.bak` (single retained backup generation) and
+  transient `journal.jsonl.tmp` (staging file, fsynced then renamed).
+- StateSnapshotJournalEvent (FR-E83): `{ ...envelope, kind:
+  "state_snapshot", snapshot_version: 1, state: RunState, node_dirs:
+  Record<nodeId, nodeDir>, events_covered: number }` — written only by
+  compaction; subsumes the journal prefix.
+- WorkflowDefaults (FR-E83): `journal_compaction_threshold_events?: number`
+  — non-negative integer, `0` disables, default 500; workflow-level only
+  (node `settings` reject the key).
+
+## Logic
+
+- **Durable Lifecycle Replay (FR-E69):** `run-journal.ts` owns the
+  recovery surface. Writer appends enveloped JSON lines with monotonic `seq`
+  and deterministic `event_id`, continuing after existing valid records on
+  resume. Fresh runs write ordinary bootstrap facts, not a snapshot blob.
+  Replay reads only the run directory, ignores duplicate `event_id`s and a
+  malformed partial tail, fails on malformed non-tail lines, and derives
+  `RunState`. Terminal records beat stale non-terminal run facts; later
+  terminal facts can supersede earlier ones. Dashboard and resume replay the
+  journal rather than `state.json`.
+- **Journal Snapshots + Crash-Safe Compaction (FR-E83):** The same
+  replayer in `run-journal.ts` (single source of replay truth) seeds from
+  the LATEST `state_snapshot` event and applies only events after it;
+  journals without snapshots replay as before; `snapshot_version` newer
+  than supported fails replay naming the journal path + version (never
+  silently skipped). Replay returns a canonically-ordered `RunState`
+  (`normalizeRunState`) so `snapshot + tail` replay is JSON byte-equal to
+  full-journal replay. Compaction (`state/journal-compaction.ts`,
+  `compactRunJournal`) is shared by engine and CLI and follows exactly:
+  (1) replay current journal → (2) write `journal.jsonl.tmp` = one
+  snapshot event, zero tail → (3) fsync tmp → (4) copy journal to
+  `journal.jsonl.bak` (one generation) → (5) atomic rename tmp over
+  `journal.jsonl`. The journal is mutated only by the final rename, so a
+  crash at any intermediate point leaves a replayable journal (old or new
+  content, never neither). Refusals (clear error, nothing modified): run
+  lock held by a live process for the run id (skipped for the engine's
+  own lock via `callerHoldsLock`), or a journal that does not replay
+  cleanly beyond torn-line tolerance; torn trailing lines — including
+  immediately after the snapshot — keep working. Engine auto-trigger:
+  `Engine.maybeCompactJournal()` runs at level/chunk completion (a
+  node-completion boundary with no node in flight — never mid-node) when
+  `RunJournalWriter.eventsSinceSnapshot` exceeds
+  `defaults.journal_compaction_threshold_events` (0 = off, default 500),
+  then re-opens the writer (seq continues after the snapshot) and emits a
+  single verbose line. CLI: `flowai-workflow runs compact [--workflow
+  <dir>] --run <runId> [--dry-run]` — dry-run reports event counts/byte
+  sizes and modifies nothing; success prints exactly one summary line
+  mentioning `journal.jsonl.bak`; failures exit non-zero with a one-line
+  error.
