+### 3.83 FR-E83: Journal State Snapshots & Crash-Safe Compaction
+
+- **Description:** The durable run journal (`journal.jsonl`, FR-E69) supports
+  a `state_snapshot` event kind carrying `snapshot_version: 1`, the complete
+  replayed run model (run status/metadata, per-node statuses and facts,
+  declared nodes, costs), declared node directories (`node_dirs`), and
+  `events_covered`. The single replayer in `src/state/run-journal.ts` seeds
+  from the LATEST valid snapshot and applies only events after it; journals
+  without snapshots replay exactly as before; a snapshot with an unsupported
+  `snapshot_version` fails replay with an error naming the journal path and
+  version. A crash-safe compaction operation — shared by engine and CLI —
+  truncates the replay prefix in exactly this order: (1) replay current
+  journal; (2) write `journal.jsonl.tmp` = one snapshot event, zero tail;
+  (3) fsync tmp; (4) copy journal to `journal.jsonl.bak` (one generation);
+  (5) atomically rename tmp over `journal.jsonl`. Compaction refuses (clear
+  error, nothing modified) when the run lock is held by a live process or
+  the journal does not replay cleanly beyond torn-line tolerance. The engine
+  auto-compacts at node-completion boundaries only (never mid-node) when
+  events since the last snapshot exceed
+  `defaults.journal_compaction_threshold_events` (non-negative integer; 0 =
+  disabled; default 500), emitting a single verbose line. Manual surface:
+  `flowai-workflow runs compact [--workflow <dir>] --run <runId>
+  [--dry-run]` with the exact success summary
+  `compacted <runId>: <eventsBefore> -> <eventsAfter> events, <bytesBefore>
+  -> <bytesAfter> bytes (backup: journal.jsonl.bak)`.
+- **Tasks:** [journal-snapshot-compaction](../tasks/2026/06/journal-snapshot-compaction.md)
+- **Motivation:** Long runs grow `journal.jsonl` without bound and replay
+  cost grows with it (FR-E69 accepted linear replay pending a measured
+  need). Snapshots bound replay cost while the compaction protocol keeps the
+  FR-E69 durability contract intact: at every intermediate crash point the
+  journal replays — old content or new, never neither.
+- **Acceptance criteria:**
+  - **Tests:** `lifecycle-replay_test.ts`, `journal-compaction_test.ts`,
+    `config_test.ts`, `merge_defaults_test.ts`, `engine_test.ts`,
+    `cli_test.ts`, `output_test.ts` (FR-E83; regression-locked; snapshot
+    payload, forward version refusal, latest-snapshot seeding, snapshot+tail
+    byte-equal equivalence, suffix-only replay via parse counting,
+    torn-line-after-snapshot, crash injection between every pair of
+    consecutive protocol steps, live-lock and unclean-journal refusals,
+    single `.bak` generation, threshold validation + default + no node-level
+    leak, boundary-only auto-trigger with verbose line, `--dry-run` no-op,
+    exact summary format, `--help` listing).
