+# engine: journal state snapshots with crash-safe compaction
+
+## Goal
+
+Bound `journal.jsonl` growth and replay cost for long runs by adding a
+`state_snapshot` journal event and a crash-safe compaction operation that
+truncates the replay prefix — automatic in the engine at node-completion
+boundaries and manual via `flowai-workflow runs compact` — without ever
+weakening the FR-E69 durability contract (a crashed compaction always leaves
+a journal that replays).
+
+## Overview
+
+### Context
+
+- FR-E69 made `journal.jsonl` the sole recovery surface: append-only JSONL,
+  replayed from an empty model by `src/state/run-journal.ts`
+  (`replayRunJournal`). Replay cost is linear in journal size; the original
+  task explicitly deferred compaction "unless a future task demonstrates a
+  measured need" — this is that task.
+- `RunJournalWriter.open` continues `seq` after existing valid records and
+  truncates a torn trailing line; replay tolerates a malformed partial tail
+  (`ignored_partial_tail`) but fails on malformed non-tail lines.
+- The replayed model is `RunState` (run status/metadata, args/env, per-node
+  statuses and facts, costs). `node_directory_declared` facts are validated
+  during replay but not folded into `RunState`.
+- The per-workflow run lock (`<workflowDir>/runs/.lock`, FR-E54) plus
+  `isRunLive(workflowDir, runId)` already answer "is this run held by a live
+  process".
+- `src/mcp/commands.ts` (FR-E75) is the precedent for logic shared across
+  surfaces; for compaction the shared core belongs in `src/state/` next to
+  the journal it owns, since both consumers (engine, CLI) need the identical
+  protocol.
+- Workflow-level settings live on `WorkflowDefaults`, validated in
+  `config.ts::validateSchema` (defaults branch), defaulted in
+  `DEFAULT_WORKFLOW_DEFAULTS`, kept out of per-node settings by
+  `extractNodeSettings` (guarded by `merge_defaults_test.ts`). Config drift
+  detection is FR-E7 (`config_test.ts` regression lock).
+
+### Current State
+
+- `src/state/run-journal.ts` — writer + single replayer; no snapshot kind.
+- `src/types.ts` — `RunJournalEventKind` union without `state_snapshot`.
+- `src/engine/engine.ts` — opens the writer, appends bootstrap/lifecycle
+  facts; no compaction trigger.
+- `src/cli.ts` — subcommands `run`/`init`/`answer`/`mcp`; no `runs` group.
+- No threshold config field; no `.bak`/`.tmp` journal siblings.
+
+### Constraints
+
+- The EXISTING replayer in `src/state/run-journal.ts` stays the single
+  source of replay truth — extend it; no second replayer.
+- Journals without snapshots replay exactly as before (zero behavior change
+  for old artifacts).
+- Crash-safe protocol, exactly: (1) replay current journal → (2) write
+  `journal.jsonl.tmp` = one `state_snapshot` line, zero tail → (3) fsync tmp
+  → (4) copy journal to `journal.jsonl.bak` → (5) atomic rename tmp over
+  `journal.jsonl`. Every intermediate crash leaves a replayable journal.
+- Refusals (manual path): run lock held by a live process for this run-id;
+  journal that does not replay cleanly beyond torn-line tolerance. Clear
+  error, nothing modified.
+- Exactly one `.bak` generation; summary must mention it.
+- Follow `src/cli.ts` argument-parsing style; no new dependencies; reuse
+  existing journal/state path helpers (no duplicated path construction).
+- Tests live alongside the subsystems they cover (state / config / engine /
+  CLI).
+- `deno task check` stays green. SRS registration in
+  `documents/requirements-engine/01-execution-model.md` + SDS journal
+  contract update.
+- Equivalence invariant: `snapshot + tail` replay deeply equals full-journal
+  replay; the dedicated test compares the two replayed run models'
+  `JSON.stringify` outputs for byte equality. (The `events` array of
+  `RunJournalReplayResult` necessarily differs — the compacted file no
+  longer contains pre-snapshot lines — so the byte-equality contract is on
+  the reconstructed run model, which is what replay exists to produce. To
+  make byte equality hold for ANY run, replay returns a canonically
+  normalized `RunState`: fixed key order, no `undefined`-valued keys.)
+
+## Definition of Done
+
